name: Standing Up For Love
description: Standing Up For Love, the debut album from reggae legend Vince Black, is a powerful and uplifting fusion of reggae, rock, and soul. Black has been backing up reggae’s finest acts for over 30 years, and is now out on his own! You can hear several tracks from the album and see his music video all on his myspace page

name: Salon d'Esoterica (Liquid Love)
description: Salon d’Esoterica (Liquid Love) is the second offering from Eugene, Oregon’s I-chele & The Circle of Light, and the first with Camp Creek Records. The record is a sensuous blend of roots, rock and reggea. It’s “what you might expect if Sade switched from jazzy R&B to reggae” (Vanessa Salvia – Eugene Weekly). Listen to some tracks at her MySpace page
